    "created_at": "2016-08-27T13:52:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-27T13:52:36Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There must be some transition tick where the current activity is not `MovePart` (probably just `Move`) even though the actor is moving. We can't just add `Move` to [line 347](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/bleed/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Activities/Move/Move.cs#L347), as that causes other regressions.\n\nAn idea I'd like to throw into the open:\nMaybe we could/should refactor the `IsMoving` check to ignore the `Move` activities entirely and only check for horizontal position changes.\nThen we'd need some kind of `BlockAnimation` boolean for special cases like troops on TD landing craft, troops transported by carryalls and teleporting, of course, but that still sounds easier to me than messing around with `Move`.\n"
  },
